    "title": "Trump fills cabinet spots after selecting Rollins as agriculture chief",
    "text": "WASHINGTON (TNND) — President-elect Donald Trump announced his pick for U.S. Secretary of Agriculture, completing his nominee spots for his cabinet . On Saturday, Trump announced that Texan Brooke L. Rollins will oversee the country's agency that controls policies, regulations, and aid programs related to farming, forestry, ranching, food quality and nutrition. As our next Secretary of Agriculture, Brooke will spearhead the effort to protect American Farmers, who are truly the backbone of our Country. Congratulations Brooke! Rollins currently heads the Trump-allies America First Policy Institute \"building a team of loyal Patriots.\" He stated that Rollins developed and managed the transformational domestic policy agenda of his administration. She was the director of Trump's Office of American Innovation during his first-term in the Oval Office. The nomination must be confirmed by the Republican-led Senate. Rollins would succeed President Joe Biden’s agriculture secretary, Tom Vilsack. Rollins graduated from Texas A&M University with a a Bachelor’s of Science Degree in Agriculture Development.",
